cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on image recognition of multiple food items, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of hierarchical recognition and limited availability of training data suggests a potential application of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Additionally, the use of menu changes and the need for accurate recognition in a restaurant setting could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in the form of menu descriptions and potentially labeling food items.
